{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"edb16830-2067-464d-bb76-9de468dc9db4","content":"You can filter by class name using the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nOr filter by class directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"ClassName=ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The second form does an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a41ebf35-092f-46c9-8213-eba8828d625c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. Let me check the test file to understand the structure.","outputTokens":161,"requestId":"4C61:5645A:1024F1E:12FB608:6A013052"},"id":"8676c9e5-95be-4df4-a615-91c31a1bdc92","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:26:46.552Z","parentId":"14069509-078d-4620-b2dc-120bbae89bcc"}
